title: setup.py and requirements.txt not working
body:
I have python 3.8.5 installed and I tried running 
`python setup.py develop`
during running I got error

> AttributeError: 'dict' object has no attribute '__NUMPY_SETUP__'
and then another error
`During handling of the above exception, another exception occurred:

`Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "setup.py", line 89, in <module>
    setup(
  File "C:\Users\tarandeep singh\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python38-32\lib\site-packages\setuptools\__init__.py", line 144, in setup
    return distutils.core.setup(**attrs)
  File "C:\Users\tarandeep singh\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python38-32\lib\distutils\core.py", line 148, in setup
    dist.run_commands()
  File "C:\Users\tarandeep singh\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python38-32\lib\distutils\dist.py", line 966, in run_commands
    self.run_command(cmd)
  File "C:\Users\tarandeep singh\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python38-32\lib\distutils\dist.py", line 985, in run_command
    cmd_obj.run()
  File "setup.py", line 55, in run
    setuptools.command.develop.develop.run(self)
  File "C:\Users\tarandeep singh\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python38-32\lib\site-packages\setuptools\command\develop.py", line 38, in run
    self.install_for_development()
`

i also tried `pip install -r requirements.txt`

`$ pip install -r requirements.txt
ERROR: Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement torch>=1.5 (from -r requirements.txt (line 1)) (from versions: 0.1.2, 0.1.2.post1, 0.1.2.post2)
ERROR: No matching distribution found for torch>=1.5 (from -r requirements.txt (line 1))
`
